#: src/contributing.md:1
msgid "Contributing"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:3
msgid "Contributions are welcome, and they are greatly appreciated!"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:5
msgid "You can contribute in many ways:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:7
msgid "Types of Contributions"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:9
msgid "Report Bugs"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:11
msgid ""
"Report bugs at [https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/issues](https://github.com/"
"PyO3/maturin/issues)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:13
msgid "Fix Bugs"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:15
msgid ""
"Look through the GitHub issues for bugs. Anything tagged with `bug` and "
"`help wanted` is open to whoever wants to implement it."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:18
msgid "Implement Features"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:20
msgid "Look through the GitHub issues for features."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:22
msgid "Write Documentation"
msgstr "撰寫文件"

#: src/contributing.md:24
msgid ""
"Maturin could always use more documentation, whether as part of the official "
"guide, in docstrings or even on the web in blog posts, articles and such."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:27
msgid "Submit Feedback"
msgstr "提交意見反饋"

#: src/contributing.md:29
msgid ""
"The best way to send feedback is to start a new discussion at [https://"
"github.com/PyO3/maturin/discussions](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/"
"discussions)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:32
msgid "Get Started!"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:34
msgid "Ready to contribute? Here's how to setup maturin for local development."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:36
msgid "Fork the maturin repository on GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:37
msgid "Clone your fork locally:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:41
msgid ""
"[Install a stable Rust toolchain](https://www.rust-lang.org/tools/install) "
"and of course [Python 3.6 or later is also required](https://realpython.com/"
"installing-python/)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:43
msgid "Create a branch for local development:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:48
msgid "Now you can make your changes locally."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:49
msgid ""
"When you're done making changes, format your changes with `cargo fmt`, then "
"lint with `cargo clippy` and test them with `cargo test`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:56
msgid ""
"Note that in order to run tests you need to install `virtualenv` and `cffi` "
"(`pip3 install cffi virtualenv`)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:58
msgid "Commit your changes and push your branch to GitHub:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:64
msgid ""
"Submit a pull request through the [GitHub website](https://github.com/PyO3/"
"maturin/pulls)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:66
msgid ""
"We provides a pre-configured [dev container](https://containers.dev/) that "
"could be used in [Github Codespaces](https://github.com/features/"
"codespaces), [VSCode](https://code.visualstudio.com/), [JetBrains](https://"
"www.jetbrains.com/remote-development/gateway/), [JuptyerLab](https://"
"jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/stable/)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:68
msgid ""
"[![Open in GitHub Codespaces](https://github.com/codespaces/badge.svg)]"
"(https://codespaces.new/pyo3/maturin?quickstart=1&machine=standardLinux32gb)"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:70
msgid "Pull Request Guidelines"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:72
msgid "Before you submit a pull request, check that it meets these guidelines:"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:74
msgid ""
"The pull request should include tests if it adds or changes functionalities."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:75
msgid ""
"Add a [changelog](https://github.com/PyO3/maturin/blob/main/Changelog.md) "
"entry."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:77
msgid ""
"When command line interface changes, run `python3 test-crates/update_readme."
"py` to update related documentation."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:79
msgid "Code"
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:81
msgid ""
"The main part is the maturin library, which is completely documented and "
"should be well integrable. The accompanying `main.rs` takes care username "
"and password for the pypi upload and otherwise calls into the library."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:83
msgid ""
"The `sysconfig` folder contains the output of `python -m sysconfig` for "
"different python versions and platform, which is helpful during development."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:85
msgid ""
"You need to install `cffi` and `virtualenv` (`pip install cffi virtualenv`) "
"to run the tests."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:87
msgid ""
"You can set the `MATURIN_TEST_PYTHON` environment variable to run the tests "
"against a specific Python version, for example "
"`MATURIN_TEST_PYTHON=python3.11 cargo test` will run the tests against "
"Python 3.11."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:90
msgid ""
"There are some optional hacks that can speed up the tests (over 80s to 17s "
"on my machine)."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:91
msgid ""
"By running `cargo build --release --manifest-path test-crates/cargo-mock/"
"Cargo.toml` you can activate a cargo cache avoiding to rebuild the pyo3 test "
"crates with every python version."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:92
msgid ""
"Delete `target/test-cache` to clear the cache (e.g. after changing a test "
"crate) or remove `test-crates/cargo-mock/target/release/cargo` to deactivate "
"it."
msgstr ""

#: src/contributing.md:93
msgid ""
"By running the tests with the `faster-tests` feature, binaries are stripped "
"and wheels are only stored and not compressed."
msgstr ""
